## Change 3 of 5: `src/channels/telegram.ts` — Add `/reset` command

**Acceptance Criteria:** AC-3.1 through AC-3.6

### Change 3a: Extend `TelegramChannelOpts` interface (line 15-19)

**Before:**
```typescript
export interface TelegramChannelOpts {
  onMessage: OnInboundMessage;
  onChatMetadata: OnChatMetadata;
  registeredGroups: () => Record<string, RegisteredGroup>;
}
```

**After:**
```typescript
export interface TelegramChannelOpts {
  onMessage: OnInboundMessage;
  onChatMetadata: OnChatMetadata;
  registeredGroups: () => Record<string, RegisteredGroup>;
  onReset?: (chatJid: string, groupFolder: string) => Promise<void>;
}
```

### Change 3b: Add `/reset` command handler (after line 81, after the `/ping` handler)

Insert between line 81 (`});` closing `/ping` handler) and line 83 (`// Telegram bot commands handled above`):

```typescript
    // Command to reset the Claude session for this chat
    this.bot.command('reset', async (ctx) => {
      const chatJid = `tg:${ctx.chat.id}`;
      const group = this.opts.registeredGroups()[chatJid];
      if (!group) {
        ctx.reply('This chat is not registered with any bot group.');
        return;
      }
      if (this.opts.onReset) {
        await this.opts.onReset(chatJid, group.folder);
        ctx.reply(
          'Session reset. Next message starts a fresh conversation.\n\n' +
          '_Your message history and knowledge base are preserved._',
          { parse_mode: 'Markdown' },
        );
      } else {
        ctx.reply('Reset is not available.');
      }
    });
```

### Change 3c: Add `'reset'` to `TELEGRAM_BOT_COMMANDS` set (line 85)

**Before:**
```typescript
    const TELEGRAM_BOT_COMMANDS = new Set(['chatid', 'ping']);
```

**After:**
```typescript
    const TELEGRAM_BOT_COMMANDS = new Set(['chatid', 'ping', 'reset']);
```

### What These Changes Do

- 3a: Adds an optional `onReset` callback to the opts interface. Optional so existing code that constructs `TelegramChannelOpts` without `onReset` continues to compile.
- 3b: Registers `/reset` as a Telegram bot command. When invoked, it looks up the chat's registered group, calls the `onReset` callback, and replies with confirmation. If the chat isn't registered or `onReset` isn't provided, it replies with an appropriate error.
- 3c: Prevents `/reset` from also being stored as a regular message (same pattern as `/chatid` and `/ping`).

### New Test: `src/channels/telegram.test.ts`

Add to the existing test file, following the pattern of the `/chatid` tests:

