**What this does:** Instead of using the startup-cached `oauthToken`, calls `readOAuthToken()` at request time. Every OAuth exchange request reads the freshest token from disk. If the token can't be read, logs an error (the request will fail with 401 from Anthropic, which is better than silently succeeding with a stale token).

### Change 1e: Update startup log to show credentials source (line 113)

**Before (line 112-114):**
```typescript
    server.listen(port, host, () => {
      logger.info({ port, host, authMode }, 'Credential proxy started');
