**Problem: double scheduling.** Change 1g calls `scheduleTokenRefresh()` inside `startCredentialProxy`, and this section calls it again from `index.ts`.

**Solution: Two-phase scheduling.** The proxy starts an early, non-alerting schedule immediately (to protect against token expiry during channel setup). Once channels are connected, `index.ts` re-schedules WITH alerting. The `scheduleTokenRefresh()` function clears any existing timer before setting a new one, so the second call safely replaces the first.

### Change 2c-i: Update `scheduleTokenRefresh` to clear existing timer on re-entry

**In `src/credential-proxy.ts`, add to the top of `scheduleTokenRefresh()`:**

```typescript
export function scheduleTokenRefresh(
  credentialsPath?: string,
  onAlert?: (message: string) => void,
): void {
  // Clear any existing timer (safe to call multiple times)
  stopTokenRefresh();
  alertFn = onAlert;
  // ... rest of function unchanged
```

